The paper presents a modeling language for Component & Connector architectures, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE). The language is designed for modeling interactive distributed and cyber-physical systems, which suggests a focus on distributed computing (cs.DC) and systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of a DSL framework, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of tools for the language, which could fall under the category of architecture and design (cs.AR).
